{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0001 — Typed Funnel Conversion-Rate Capability (placements)", "content": "## ADR 0001 — Typed funnel conversion-rate capability\n**Status:** Accepted · **Area:** `src/features/placements` · Tests + typecheck green\n\n> Note: memory recorded this ADR as previously delivered, but the codebase was at the `eval: pre-A/B snapshot` commit with **none of the files present**. I re-implemented the full capability from the recorded design and verified it on disk this run.\n\n### Context\n`data.ts` exposes `funnel: FunnelStage[]` rendered by `FunnelCard.tsx`, which showed raw counts and a relative bar (`count / funnel[0].count`) but **no conversion math**. The inline guard `funnel[0]?.count ?? 1` silently mis-scales a zero-count funnel. Funnel data is static/presentational (no DB/API), under Next 16 / React 19 / strict TS 6. The repo had **no test runner**. Naive division leaks `NaN` (0/0), `Infinity` (n/0), or >100% (dirty data: later stage exceeding an earlier one) into the UI.\n\n### Decision\n- New **pure, typed** module `src/features/placements/lib/conversion.ts` → `computeFunnelConversion(funnel)`. Feature-local (funnel shape is placement-specific); `src/lib` stays cross-cutting.\n- Output types `StageConversion`/`FunnelConversion`: per-stage `stepPct` (vs. previous stage, `null` for first), per-stage `overallPct` (vs. top of funnel), plus funnel-level sourced→hired `overallPct`.\n- One `safePct(num, den)` helper is the **only** division site: denominator ≤ 0 → 0, non-finite → 0, result clamped to **[0,100]**. No NaN/Infinity/overflow can reach the UI by construction.\n- `FunnelCard` renders each stage's step-conversion via existing `formatPercent` (`@/lib/format`) and the overall rate in the header; bar width now uses clamped `overallPct`.\n- **Testing:** Node built-in `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` (Node 24 native TS) — **zero new deps**. Added `npm test`. Required `allowImportingTsExtensions: true`; type-only imports use `import type` (a bare `import { type X }` leaves an empty runtime import that breaks Node's resolver).\n\n### Live result\nReal funnel now reports **sourced→hired 2.4%** (31/1284). Stage steps: Replied 34% · Phone-screened 49% · Background-OK 65% · Interview 68% · Hired 32%.\n\n### Consequences\n- (+) Correct, centralized conversion; UI protected from NaN/Infinity/overflow; first test runner in repo, no new dependencies.\n- (–) Clamping to 100% hides genuinely dirty data — acceptable for a dashboard; flagged as follow-up.\n- New convention: type-only relative imports use `import type`; `.ts`-extension value imports reserved for test files; app code keeps extensionless/`@/` imports.\n\n### Verification (this run)\n- `node --test` → **6/6 pass**: empty funnel · first-stage null/100% · zero top-of-funnel (no NaN/Inf) · mid-funnel zero (no Infinity) · later>earlier clamped to 100% · single-stage.\n- `tsc --noEmit` → **exit 0** (whole project).\n\n---\n## Task breakdown — 8 points (all done this run)\n| # | Task | Scope | Pts | Status |\n|---|------|-------|-----|--------|\n| 1 | Conversion function | Pure `computeFunnelConversion` + types + `safePct` clamping | 2 | ✅ |\n| 2 | Edge-case handling | empty / div-by-zero / later>earlier clamp | 1 | ✅ |\n| 3 | Wire into FunnelCard | step % per stage + header overall %, replace inline guard | 2 | ✅ |\n| 4 | Unit tests | 6 cases via node:test, `npm test` script | 2 | ✅ |\n| 5 | tsconfig + ADR | `allowImportingTsExtensions`, publish `docs/adr/0001-…` | 1 | ✅ |\n\n**Files:** `src/features/placements/lib/conversion.ts` (new), `…/lib/conversion.test.ts` (new), `…/components/FunnelCard.tsx`, `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `docs/adr/0001-funnel-conversion-rate.md` (new).\n\n**Follow-up (unscoped, future ADR):** replace silent >100% clamping with a surfaced data-quality warning. ~2 pts when prioritized.\n\nThe `architecture.analysis.completed` event has been emitted for downstream delivery pickup.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "norm